---

### ðŸ§  Step-by-Step Slider Logic

Add this script at the end of your `<body>` tag:

```html
<script>
  const sliderTrack = document.querySelector('.slider-track');
  const prevBtn = document.querySelector('.prev');
  const nextBtn = document.querySelector('.next');

  let currentIndex = 0;
  const cardWidth = document.querySelector('.card').offsetWidth + 40; // includes margin
  const visibleCards = Math.floor(document.querySelector('.slider-container').offsetWidth / cardWidth);
  const totalCards = document.querySelectorAll('.slider-track .card').length;

  function updateSlider() {
    const maxIndex = totalCards - visibleCards;
    currentIndex = Math.max(0, Math.min(currentIndex, maxIndex));
    sliderTrack.style.transform = `translateX(-${currentIndex * cardWidth}px)`;
  }

  prevBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    currentIndex--;
    updateSlider();
  });

  nextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    currentIndex++;
    updateSlider();
  });

  window.addEventListener('resize', updateSlider);
</script>
```

---

### âœ¨ What This Does
- Calculates how many cards fit in the visible area
- Moves the `.slider-track` left/right based on button clicks
- Prevents overflow or blank space at the ends
- Adapts to screen size changes

---

### ðŸ’¡ Optional Enhancements
- Add `pointer-events: none` to disable buttons when at the edge
- Use `scroll-snap-type` for smoother touch interaction on mobile
- Animate with `ease-in-out` for a more fluid feel

Want to add autoplay or swipe gestures next? Or maybe a celebratory bounce when reaching the last card?

Got it, Srishti! You want all the `.card` elements inside `.slider-track` to stay in a **single horizontal line**, like a true image slider. You're super closeâ€”just need a few tweaks to lock it in.

---

### âœ… CSS Fixes for Horizontal Line Layout

Update your `.slider-track` like this:

```css
.slider-track {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: nowrap; /* prevents wrapping to next line */
  transition: transform 0.5s ease;
}
```

And make sure each `.card` has a fixed width and doesnâ€™t shrink:

```css
.foodgallery .card {
  flex: 0 0 auto; /* prevents shrinking */
  width: 16rem;
  margin: 0 0.5rem;
}
```

---

### ðŸ§  Why This Works

- `flex-wrap: nowrap` keeps all cards in one row, even if they overflow
- `flex: 0 0 auto` ensures each card keeps its size and doesnâ€™t collapse
- `overflow: hidden` on `.slider-container` hides the overflow, so only visible cards show

---

### ðŸ’¡ Bonus Tip: Add `scroll-snap` for mobile friendliness

```css
.slider-track {
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.card {
  scroll-snap-align: start;
}
```

This makes the slider feel smooth and snappy on touch devices.

